As I continue my endless endeavor to help and assist the less fortunate then I, I sit by the main lift in Kelethin and read a communiqué that I just received from Velious.  It states that He fell in battle against the Frost Giants but was favored enough to receive a rez from a wandering cleric.  Blessed be Tunare!  The Shadow Knight lives to see another day.  <br>
<br>
But how sad it is, that He is not welcomed in my beautiful city.  To be able to show Him the lyrical beauty of my ever so peaceful home.  My eyes fill with tears…”How can it be?  How can a druid of gentle heart be captivated by one that is without remorse towards the druid race and the bunnies in Eastern Wastes?” he he..I smile. He loves to tease me. <br>
<br>
Later in the day, I packed my backpacks and ported to Shadow Haven to meet with Deknyr and help him with one of his many quests.  This sweet druid friend is so intent in completing the many quests he has at hand, he puts me to shame he he.  As I reach the bank to meet Dek, a cold shiver go up my spine as I have this strange feeling that someone is watching me.  I turn around but see nothing shady.  Is it Him?  I enter the bank and smile at Dek as he roughly hands over a backpack full of pelts.  “Come on girl, we don’t have all day!”<br>
