<br>
As I last slept my dreams were troubled. Whispers of deception, and hatred towards me. Will I ever know why such things haunt me so? Why oh why do the whispers in my dreams lead to mistrust of my fellow dragons, and to mistrust of my friends? Is this the price I must pay for the knowledge of who it was that betrayed my family so long ago?<br>
<br>
I cling to Amber tighter. I must sleep and not have such troubled dreams. My fellow dragons are my frineds. They would not do any of the things that the whispers implied. They will not throw me to the wolves to survive on my own.<br>
<br>
With my mind reeling, I force myself to sleep once again. Maybe this time will bring happy dreams. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Scale</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/18/03 5:24:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: </span><hr size=1> Watching over Selicatiren - I wonder truelly who has hurt this warm and kind soul.  What does she need?  Mummering words of magick I place a spell of contentment on her - safe guards on every spot a enemy could enter - whispering to Amber to guard well and keep this child of mine safe - I then raise my arms opening a gate and poof I am gone - the only visible mark to tell of my visit is the magic crystal hung on her window - catching the moonlight to cast away any shadows in the room and in her mind....<br>
