<br>
I then raise my arms opening a gate and poof I am gone - the only visible mark to tell of my visit is the magic crystal hung on her window - catching the moonlight to cast away any shadows in the room and in her mind....<br>
<br>
Slipping between my silken sheets - the days worrys driving deep in my mind - dropping my lantern my shield my clothes in ever direction - quickly - I snuggle up to the warm body waiting for me - Peraspera, my heart my love - sticking my cold feet up againist him I drift to sleep...finally with him I find comfort. <br>
